          "abstract": "<jats:p>In order to study the agrotechnology of okra cultivation for fiber production in the conditions of our republic, a study was conducted on the development of 10 different varieties of the plant in field conditions on typical gray soils of the Tashkent region. The best development indicators were observed in the Argentine varieties “K-338” and “K-207”, Bangladeshi “K-147”, Ghanaian “K-283”, with a height of 154-160 cm, the number of tubers 46-58, the number of inflorescences 4-9, the number of flowers 2-5 and the yield 2-4. When chemically determining the plant fiber, the average fiber yield was 10.6%, α-cellulose - 53.3%.</jats:p>",
